<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - 12/06/1994 and After - SPECIFICATIONS - AIR
        CONDITIONING SYSTEM
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEM</title>
        <table id="t1601602">
            <title>Air Conditioning System</title>
            <tgroup cols="2" colsep="1" rowsep="0">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="3.49in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="2.68in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="2" spanname="1to2"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry valign="bottom">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Refrigerant Type</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry valign="bottom">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">R-134a</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Refrigerant Quantity (Full Charge)*</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>3.5 lbs. (1.5 kg.)*</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Compressor Oil Type</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Lubrizol LZ-2916</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Compressor Oil Level</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1 inch Min. to 1-3/8 inch Max.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(Vertical Mounting)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(25.4 mm Min. to 34.9 mm Max.)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Compressor Oil Capacity**</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 oz. (340 g)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Compressor Belt Drive Tension</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Initial Tension (new Belt)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>130 lbs. (580 N)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Normal Tension (Used Belt)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>100 lbs. (450 N)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Low Pressure Switch (Normally Closed)***</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Opens At</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>24 &#177; 5 psi (166 &#177; 35 kPa)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Closes At</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>0-5 psi (0-35 kPa)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>High Pressure Switch (Normally Open)***</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Closes At</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>375 psi &#177; 20 psi (2596 &#177; 140 kPa)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Opens At</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>250 &#177; 50 psi (1725 &#177;
                                <emph type="underscr">+</emph>
                                345 kPa)
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Shutter Switch (Normally Closed)***</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Opens at</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>90-110 psi (620-760 kPa)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Closes at</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>240-260 psi (1660-1800 kPa)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Fan Drive Switch (Normally Closed)***</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Opens at</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>300 psi &#177; 10 psi</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Closes at</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>210 psi &#177; 10 psi</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="1to2">
                            <para>* 8000 Series cabs with sleeper boxes require 4.5 lbs. (2.0 kg) of R-134a. This is the
                                only exception.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="1to2">
                            <para>**When a system is being replaced with all new components or following a complete
                                flush of the system, add 2 oz. (55 g.) additional refrigerant oil.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="1to2">
                            <para>***Normally open or closed means the state of the device not being installed. The
                                operating condition may or may not be the same. Normally open in a switch is opposite
                                that in a valve. In a switch, the contacts are open and no current is conducted. In a
                                valve, the poppet is open and air flows from the inlet port to the outlet port. Normally
                                closed in a switch is the opposite of that in a valve. In a switch, the contacts are
                                closed and current is conducted. In a valve, the poppet is closed and airflow is
                                shut-off from the inlet port to the outlet port.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
